 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 02_Expertise_Analysis.ipynb\n",
    "\n",
    "## Expertise Analysis: Mapping Master's Degree Modules to Real-World Applications\n",
    "\n",
    "This Jupyter notebook delves into the specialized knowledge gained during the Master's degree in Business Administration and Engineering: Electrical Power Engineering (M.Sc. RWTH). It maps academic modules to real-world applications, including renewables simulations, crypto finance models, and interactive links to world knowledge such as Reinforcement Learning (RL) in smart grids.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Objective\n",
    "To provide a comprehensive analysis of how the Master's degree curriculum directly translates into practical expertise relevant to the renewables migration, the role at DB InfraGO AG, and the broader energy landscape.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define paths\n",
    "base_path = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), os.pardir))\n",
    "csv_path = os.path.join(base_path, 'data', 'key_details.csv')\n",
    "plots_path = os.path.join(base_path, 'plots')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure plots directory exists\n",
    "os.makedirs(plots_path, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"CSV Path: {csv_path}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Plots Path: {plots_path}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 1: Load Key Details from CSV\n",
    "We will load the `key_details.csv` to access the module information and grades.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "key_details_df = pd.read_csv(csv_path)\n",
    "# display(key_details_df.head()) # Display the first few rows\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 2: Analyze Grades Distribution\n",
    "Visualizing the distribution of grades across different academic areas provides a quick overview of performance and specialization.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Insights for Engineers (Tech Depth):** A strong performance in core engineering modules indicates a solid technical foundation, crucial for tackling complex problems in smart grids and renewable energy systems.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter for module grades (excluding 'passed' or 'X')\n",
    "grades_df = key_details_df[key_details_df['detail_key'].str.contains('Grade') & \n",
    "                           ~key_details_df['detail_value'].isin(['passed', 'X', 'ausreichend', 'befriedigend', 'gut', 'sehr gut'])]\n",
    "grades_df['detail_value'] = pd.to_numeric(grades_df['detail_value'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "grades_df = grades_df.dropna(subset=['detail_value'])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))\n",
    "sns.histplot(grades_df['detail_value'], bins=np.arange(1, 5.5, 0.5), kde=True, color='skyblue')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Module Grades (M.Sc. RWTH)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Grade (1.0 = best, 5.0 = worst)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Modules')\n",
    "plt.xticks(np.arange(1, 5.5, 0.5))\n",
    "plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.savefig(os.path.join(plots_path, 'grades_distribution.png'))\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 3: Module Mappings to Real-World Applications\n",
    "This section maps specific modules and thesis topics to their direct relevance in real-world scenarios, highlighting the practical applicability of the acquired knowledge.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Insights for Technicians (Implementation Steps):** Understanding these mappings helps in identifying how theoretical knowledge translates into actionable steps for deploying and managing complex systems, such as those in energy infrastructure or cyber-physical security.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "module_to_application = {\n",
    "    'Data Modeling in a Cross-domain Ontology for Cyber Intelligence in Smart Grids Using Reinforcement Learning': [\n",
    "        'Smart Grid Cyber Security Protocols',\n",
    "        'Reinforcement Learning for Grid Optimization',\n",
    "        'Ontology-driven Data Integration for Energy Systems'\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'Future Energy System - Part 1: Power Generation from Renewable Energies': [\n",
    "        'Renewable Energy Integration Simulations',\n",
    "        'Decentralized Energy Management Systems',\n",
    "        'Policy Frameworks for Renewable Deployment'\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'Energy Storage Systems': [\n",
    "        'Battery Energy Storage System (BESS) Design',\n",
    "        'Grid-scale Energy Storage Optimization',\n",
    "        'Hybrid Energy Storage Solutions'\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'Introduction to Cryptocurrencies, Blockchain and Decentralized Finance [Current Topic]': [\n",
    "        'Blockchain for Energy Trading',\n",
    "        'Decentralized Energy Market Models',\n",
    "        'Tokenization of Renewable Energy Assets'\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'Fehler und Stabilität in Elektrizitätsversorgungssystemen': [\n",
    "        'Grid Stability Analysis and Control',\n",
    "        'Fault Detection and Isolation in Power Systems',\n",
    "        'Resilience Engineering for Critical Infrastructure'\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'Sustainable Finance': [\n",
    "        'Green Finance Strategies',\n",
    "        'ESG Investing in Energy Sector',\n",
    "        'Carbon Credit Markets'\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display mappings (conceptual output, can be visualized as a mindmap)\n",
    "print(\"\nModule to Real-World Application Mappings:\")\n",
    "for module, applications in module_to_application.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"- {module}:\")\n",
    "    for app in applications:\n",
    "        print(f\"  - {app}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 4: Interactive World Knowledge Links (Conceptual)\n",
    "This section would conceptually link specific expertise areas to external resources or interactive simulations, demonstrating a broader understanding of the subject matter. For example, linking RL in grids to relevant research papers or open-source simulation environments.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Insights for Politicians (Policy Impacts):** Demonstrating connections to global research and best practices reinforces the strategic importance of investing in advanced technical expertise for national energy and infrastructure policies.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "knowledge_links = {\n",
    "    'Reinforcement Learning in Smart Grids': 'https://www.energy.gov/oe/articles/reinforcement-learning-applications-smart-grid-operations',\n",
    "    'Cyber Security for Critical Infrastructure': 'https://www.cisa.gov/topics/critical-infrastructure-security',\n",
    "    'Decentralized Energy Markets': 'https://www.irena.org/solar/articles/2020/Feb/Decentralized-Renewable-Energy-Systems'\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\nInteractive World Knowledge Links:\")\n",
    "for topic, url in knowledge_links.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"- {topic}: {url}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 5: Expertise Map (Conceptual Visualization)\n",
    "A conceptual mindmap illustrating the connections between the Master's degree, the role at DB InfraGO AG, and the renewables migration. This would typically be generated using specialized visualization tools or libraries.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Conceptual data for expertise map\n",
    "nodes = [\n",
    "    ('Master Degree (RWTH)', 'Degree'),\n",
    "    ('Electrical Power Engineering', 'Specialization'),\n",
    "    ('Smart Grids', 'Expertise'),\n",
    "    ('Cyber Intelligence', 'Expertise'),\n",
    "    ('Reinforcement Learning', 'Expertise'),\n",
    "    ('Sustainability', 'Expertise'),\n",
    "    ('DB InfraGO AG', 'Role'),\n",
    "    ('Stations & Services IT', 'Role'),\n",
    "    ('Renewables Migration', 'Impact')\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "edges = [\n",
    "    ('Master Degree (RWTH)', 'Electrical Power Engineering'),\n",
    "    ('Electrical Power Engineering', 'Smart Grids'),\n",
    "    ('Electrical Power Engineering', 'Cyber Intelligence'),\n",
    "    ('Electrical Power Engineering', 'Reinforcement Learning'),\n",
    "    ('Electrical Power Engineering', 'Sustainability'),\n",
    "    ('Smart Grids', 'DB InfraGO AG'),\n",
    "    ('Cyber Intelligence', 'DB InfraGO AG'),\n",
    "    ('DB InfraGO AG', 'Stations & Services IT'),\n",
    "    ('Stations & Services IT', 'Renewables Migration'),\n",
    "    ('Smart Grids', 'Renewables Migration'),\n",
    "    ('Reinforcement Learning', 'Renewables Migration'),\n",
    "    ('Sustainability', 'Renewables Migration')\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# This is a conceptual visualization. A real mindmap would use networkx and matplotlib/graphviz.\n",
    "# For simplicity, we'll just print the conceptual structure.\n",
    "print(\"\nConceptual Expertise Map:\")\n",
    "for node, node_type in nodes:\n",
    "    print(f\"- {node} ({node_type})\")\n",
    "print(\"  Connections:\")\n",
    "for source, target in edges:\n",
    "    print(f\"    - {source} -> {target}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Conclusion\n",
    "This expertise analysis demonstrates the profound relevance of the Master's degree curriculum to current and future challenges in the energy sector. The interdisciplinary knowledge in electrical power engineering, smart grids, cyber intelligence, RL, and sustainability positions Vincenzo Ceccarelli Grimaldi as a key contributor to the renewables migration and the digital transformation of critical infrastructure.\n"
   ]
  }
